The paper deals with the use of non-orthogonal multiple access (NOMA) transmission in unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV) based communication networks, which involves topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of limited feedback schemes for practical deployment, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). The use of directional beams and user region geometries also suggests a focus on millimeter wave (cs.MM) and possibly artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques for optimizing the system.
